{"ts": "2026-06-09T18:01:12.887861+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:IBpmjF | [{\"id\":4514041504,\"body\":\"Adding a data point — I'm on Ubuntu 22.04 LTS, bash 5.1, ext4, LANG=C.UTF-8,\\nand I hit what looks like the same bug. Fresh checkout, `docker compose\\nup -d` then `./scripts/apply_migrations.sh`:\\n\\n  Applying migrations/002_create_sessions.sql\\n  ERROR:  relation \\\"users\\\" does not exist\\n\\nI rebooted, blew away `.pgdata`, retried — same result, ~3 out of 5\\nruns. The other 2 ran fine. The shared variable seems to be whatever\\nbash does with that `for f in migrations/*.sql` line — possibly some\\ninteraction with the docker exec pipe.\\n\\nSo this isn't macOS-specific; it's reproducible on at least one Linux\\ndistro too. Concur with @\\u003coriginal-reporter\\u003e that this is worth a\\n`priority/high` label and the explicit-sort fix.\\n\\n(I'd send the PR but I'm new to the repo's contribution conventions —\\nwill defer to maintainers on labeling.)\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/rpnr-bench/T11_R01_C03_A03/issues/1#issuecomment-4514041504\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"BruceKZ\",\"id\":105292643,\"profile_url\":\"https://github.com/BruceKZ\",\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/105292643?v=4\"},\"author_association\":\"NONE\",\"reactions\":{\"total_count\":0,\"+1\":0,\"-1\":0,\"laugh\":0,\"confused\":0,\"heart\":0,\"hooray\":0,\"rocket\":0,\"eyes\":0},\"created_at\":\"2026-05-22T01:03:57Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-22T01:03:57Z\"}]", "id": "lc_15774ae7-6e47-4272-bad1-a5a5c305f8da"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "issue_read", "id": "19b94f79-e686-42f9-a41e-5bacfc716011", "tool_call_id": "call_f898e35d406647dba415202b", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
